elements.2211.03018_5924edad82f10a1f9840108f11fe9: Depth-based Sampling and Steering Constraints for Memoryless Local Planners]
elements.2211.03018_c2696d92b8d5e3f7db7cebe7255bd: In recent years, depth cameras have become available and more affordable, increasing their usage for robotic applications in the industrial and the research community
elements.2211.03018_b1c3c6f3b3f67f61b13d7f17f8de9: One interesting use case is on quadrotors, where onboard depth sensors generate data for obstacle avoidance algorithms (path planners) to keep the drone safe
elements.2211.03018_dbe4f1d8d666d3a248d84f273563c: Many research groups have employed depth data in their studies on path planning for quadrotors
elements.2211.03018_1e1eb7b349fd6bf7a16dc010512c1: However, those depth data remain underutilised in existing works, giving us an opportunity to further exploit them to increase sampling efficiency and path planning performance.
elements.2211.03018_ccd256237e592357e65660163c97f: The sampling-based technique is ubiquitously used as a trajectory planning approach for quadrotors in unstructured environments
elements.2211.03018_e9b46a71e0dfa70aef284d20dca27: ; however, the number of sampled collision-free trajectories is limited
elements.2211.03018_82adef9fa90f91451110638de47f0: A sampled set with a large percentage of in-collision candidates will require a significant amount of computational power on collision checking
elements.2211.03018_f7ced9149e9089d6c8e4139ecacaa: exploit their piecewise triple-double integrator in time for state modelling to produce a closed-form future maneuver library
elements.2211.03018_41ac5875325659e8d8348bf469bf4: Although their probabilistic maneuver library can be quickly propagated by uniformly sampling in the state space, it can also be rich in in-collision candidates
elements.2211.03018_f525a7cd97bd69e8654ea24e13fd4: Since they utilise a k-d tree representation of local structures for the collision checking process, it requires up-front computation cost to construct that 3D structure
elements.2211.03018_11e3e845d52b3e4391291f8ab9588: Also using k-d trees for collision checking, Lopez
elements.2211.03018_8e4b5ee144444370135307e6233e6: generate a set of motion primitives specified by desired speeds and heading angles
elements.2211.03018_0a4496747c06f8f0e344d087ffc86: They uniformly sample possible headings from within the field of view (FoV) while keeping the forward speed constant
elements.2211.03018_069225f375717b9db9cda3ecaefc0: Those motion primitives can easily satisfy state constraints, such as remaining within the FoV of the sensor
elements.2211.03018_e779cf41edf01bad674146d0a8076: This approach may work effectively in environments with sparse obstacles
elements.2211.03018_1dcd29c483e1c5c24881f4cfb80fa: However, in an obstacle-dense area that would increase the binary search of a single k-d tree query, an unrefined motion primitive set can cause an exploded computation load for collision checking
elements.2211.03018_6aa1292641801c71547176127fef6: . uniformly sampled over yaw-heading and final Euclidean distance from the vehicle to generate a spatially and dynamically diverse set of motion primitives, which will also suffer from the same potential issue of heavy workload
elements.2211.03018_c8d35cc3c1416750e79d5ef4fd1a6: While the works mentioned above fuse recent depth images into a local 3D structure, RAPPIDS - Rectangular Pyramid Partitioning using Integrated Depth Sensors
elements.2211.03018_246f2b0f48fd09644381e27beedaa: is more lightweight since it exploits only the latest depth image for directly partitioning the free space using a number of rectangular pyramids
elements.2211.03018_c737b54a101a361954ed7cd0c032c: However, RAPPIDS explores the space by randomly sampling trajectories' endpoints over a given range in the sensor's FoV (sampling space), which is not carefully constrained before sampling
elements.2211.03018_4f3276f9270df01a20ca914aa0b45: This approach results in a low-quality sampled set that includes many in-collision trajectories when the quadrotor flies in an obstacle-filled area, burdening the collision checking.
elements.2211.03018_c1944ea40f322699dbb0f97604ab9: Besides computational efficiency, planning performance can also be improved by directly utilising depth data
elements.2211.03018_40ad36df327fd542be2c58ca185fe: All those previously mentioned planners are classified as mapless and memoryless algorithms
elements.2211.03018_cd95028cc7d9eaf0da5a552daef4d: only employ a local map that is just enough for local planning, and a memoryless one
elements.2211.03018_c5d0863011275c540c652b92a2ed6: Distinguishing from those, map-based planning systems
elements.2211.03018_57e210c55d73f6188b2f9c67cc9c4: and a global planning algorithm such as RRT*
elements.2211.03018_a355cbbcdc09726caa1651f3c318f: to guarantee planning completeness in tasks such as exploration,
elements.2211.03018_ddf92ee879526592fe7569e5c0b89: All mapless and memoryless planners cannot access any map but use sensor data
elements.2211.03018_7db5dc3acb3cec7d43993c5d624e3: They are likely to fail to reach the goal in cluttered environments
elements.2211.03018_2f1d17dbe07c4250ce3dd31c0e488: introduces an autonomous system employing RAPPIDS to planning trajectories toward a goal in a cluttered environment
elements.2211.03018_9a9c59f4a4ce2af128a1251f6b6ea: Their algorithm would stop planning when facing a large obstacle such as a wall
elements.2211.03018_d66ec3ccd2a4d0fc99bd205ceaa28: Therefore, there is still room for enhancement of the memoryless planner's performance and ability to autonomously plan and find a solution.
elements.2211.03018_976cf9cdc95d2ad63995ddc28be53: In those mapless and memoryless algorithms, motion primitives are sampled without considering available depth information
elements.2211.03018_ada1fbe73d3d73f0ab0f283af0b5b: We can utilise available depth data to refine the motion primitive set before it comes to collision checking
elements.2211.03018_cd186b3816716605090e9acb8dc2c: This is where our depth-based sampling method contributes
elements.2211.03018_a8d9fcc793b9a3c4a2d11e157bc54: Specifically, we find and reject obscured primitives' endpoints or constrain the sampling space only by querying depth values, automatically excluding many meaningless (in-collision) candidates in the sampled set
elements.2211.03018_3699ff50d2d375203e262c02560e9: Since this procedure can be done in constant time, our approach will reduce the computational workload required in collision checking
elements.2211.03018_c2e4aec765592b7bb6cab61eabda4: Additionally, we will promote the planning autonomy level by proposing a steering mechanism, increasing the system's success rate
elements.2211.03018_04752c2b65b38175351eb52c88453: Our steering mechanism uses a heuristic algorithm coupling with a direction utility function to offer existing memoryless planners a higher autonomy in scenarios of convex obstacles.
elements.2211.03018_b0e1a9c874c3598b53a6b45ecf53f: To evaluate our proposed approaches, we build a complete planning system that is capable of autonomously navigating a quadrotor through a cluttered environment to a given destination
elements.2211.03018_726b9c42e4bee8987f3bcdaa5c7fc: The planning system consists of only a memoryless local planner, and no explicit global planners are required
elements.2211.03018_9fdcfae209eba74e9c089bd873cd6: Results show that our depth-based steering mechanism can navigate through large-obstacle scenarios in which existing depth-based local planners will get stuck
elements.2211.03018_43a34355620334416170aa0df0a4b: That is, our approach enables successful autonomous flights toward a goal without the integration of high-level global planners
elements.2211.03018_ce516a461411fb0fbd8535b82639c: Another simulation benchmark also demonstrates that our depth-based sampling method will reach a considerably higher computational efficiency than the original uniform sampling technique used in previous works
elements.2211.03018_5c04a4a73ae7e8a7e1cb609ee435c: To the best of our knowledge, this is the first work that integrates a depth-based sampling technique and an autonomous steering mechanism within a memoryless planner framework for navigating toward a goal in unknown cluttered environments.
elements.2211.03018_e4825ced7450be7c860711c74eeac: Our contributions can be summarized as follows:
elements.2211.03018_fa49849b74508cd07eb79324bffa7: 1) We propose a depth-based sampling technique for memoryless planners to improve their computational efficiency using depth sensors.
elements.2211.03018_15e7ac719769860f69ef88be20ef7: 2) We propose a steering mechanism for an autonomous planning system
elements.2211.03018_27cbf638e2420b2b8b3cb48e35e98: The planning system is capable of autonomously navigating aerial robots through cluttered environments to a goal, without employing any external global planners
elements.2211.03018_d44ce59088b332264171a33f55ad6: Our system outperforms the previous memoryless planner
elements.2211.03018_27496dfbd3ceb81fb35a2d977ff8f: in terms of escaping large obstacles (larger than the FoV).
elements.2211.03018_d175aa68f8bfda19731df8cafe629: Mapless and memoryless planners only use a very limited dynamic memory for collision checking
elements.2211.03018_32bc133bd1d404a8dbd51b259e5fc: fuse the most recent historical sensor measurements into a local 3D data structure (e.g., k-d tree) but not an entire global map for collision checking
elements.2211.03018_1f0a9dc02722df9bc9547f9d1eb99: exploits only the latest sensor data
elements.2211.03018_7d60079b5fa01a6353e99e5b812e5: These types of planners lend themselves to local planning purposes.

elements.2211.03018_1c0b5a400f3e43572c8b8db50bc57: Each step would use different computational resources, depending on the types of planners
elements.2211.03018_39f10ef39d5f10541d1ccc1432309: For example, memoryless or mapless planners spend most of their resources on collision checking, while map-based planners may cost substantial computational power in both evaluating costs (e.g., volumetric exploration gain

elements.2211.03018_5c0a3ea366d2407780d94dd03e075: Thus, its efficiency affects the performance of the entire workflow.
elements.2211.03018_384badb12b710292ee874ab1b8a99: only offers an unrefined sample set, which might contain a number of meaningless (in-collision) candidates
elements.2211.03018_bb0a4d336c636f736c672045f2b46: Such a low-quality sampled set (low in collision-free samples) will burden the collision-checking stage, thus it can be a bottleneck to the system's performance
elements.2211.03018_cff3ed9e4fc71cc15b5bbb9fd4f83: Checking for collision is the most computationally expensive task in the pipeline as we have to manipulate memory-consuming data structures such as depth images, k-d trees or Euclidean signed distance field (ESDF)
elements.2211.03018_cd7abc9ab19e55582c789a9db4771: If the sampling space contains too many in-collision candidates, planners would cost much more computational power and time for the same given output in a planning sequence
elements.2211.03018_c14d1acfd8ea63e581c3f94881a8a: As a result, many planning sequences would have been done for nothing, e.g., wasting power and time in evaluating many trajectories that would result in a collision
elements.2211.03018_423a06cc0ec7850876d7f6eb87a3d: Therefore, refining the sampling space can be a promising technique.
elements.2211.03018_a8714aa1e79481a4f52fe3bf00d95: To lower the requirement for computing resources, we need to eliminate a certain number of in-collision candidates in the sample set by considering depth data
elements.2211.03018_85edf86affcf2afa1c1de2f0d346e: We can determine a particular type of in-collision trajectory by comparing the trajectory endpoint's position with its projection in the depth matrix
elements.2211.03018_68df3d919575f09ca5609fb94bdf2: If the endpoint is farther from the robot than its projection's depth, it is considered inside obstacles, and its trajectory is considered in-collision, and vice versa
elements.2211.03018_8de3ff0eb8904cade2321acf92e9e: By analysing the relative position between trajectories and the occupied space, we categorized them into four types: (type (0)) collision-free trajectories have their entire path outside the occupied space, (type (1)) trajectories have their endpoints too close to the occupied space (the robot will collide when getting to the endpoint), (type (2)) trajectories have their middle sections inside the occupied space and their endpoints outside (the robot will collide before getting to the endpoint) and (type (3)) trajectories have their endpoints inside the occupied space as in Fig.
elements.2211.03018_8e179c0b97ae9ae7b3ee4fa25bfdd: Although the collision-checking process can reject all types of in-collision trajectories, the fewer in-collision candidates that need to be checked, the fewer computing resources will be spent
elements.2211.03018_a47ddf3e6d9bd4227f14c2dc30503: Therefore, in this work, we will systematically exclude the type (3), obscured-endpoint candidates, by constraining the sampling space using raw depth data
elements.2211.03018_f7fe1ff233e65b646ecf1b6c4c1b8: Type (1) and type (2) will be rejected by the collision-checking step afterwards
elements.2211.03018_9e4516ba0b009136be47b4033e738: Reducing the number of in-collision candidates that require checking will reduce needed computing resources.

elements.2211.03018_57b857ac4a723f657d3dd533157e9: For local planning, motion primitives can generally be sampled in input space or state space

elements.2211.03018_ee47ed9acbbe1c48c149a6637a1bc: In this paper, we have presented the depth-based sampling and steering technique that improves memoryless planners' efficiency
elements.2211.03018_3edd8022a9df58cdd5623ac2240dd: Our proposed sampling method exploited available depth data to constrain sampling space, excluding obscured endpoint samples, which are candidates that are not meaningful (in-collision) for planning
elements.2211.03018_cf67bfad8eabf60b70980dec9e84a: Thus, the enhanced planner generates a better-cost trajectory over the same amount of allocated computation time compared with the same planner that uses the uniform sampling technique
elements.2211.03018_91d0359dc9ac6fc4c82586d3e0d48: Additionally, we built a complete planning system that adopted the proposed depth-based steering algorithm based on that advantage
elements.2211.03018_b2074fa580e4f4324a4b761602b64: The steering technique equips the local planner with the capability of autonomously escaping potential stuck motions such as large convex obstacles, enabling a higher success rate for the planning system in obstacle-dense scenarios
elements.2211.03018_101c334e958ae215cfa59590e38e7: The simulation results have demonstrated that the proposed approach outperforms the state-of-the-art technique
elements.2211.03018_0b7df9e1fef3855b33b1b6f8f4a6c: Since the adopted planner only guarantees instantaneous best direction at every planning sequence, extensions to this work may include a mechanism to translate it into a local optimal such as the shortest distance travelled or fastest time to escape one obstacle when integrating with other techniques.
